A vintage 1960s spy thriller movie poster style illustration showing a shadowy figure peering over someone's shoulder at a glowing computer screen in a dimly lit room. The screen casts an eerie blue-green glow on both faces - one unsuspecting user in the foreground, and one sinister silhouette lurking behind. The scene features a mid-century modern desk setup with an old CRT-style monitor displaying rows of glowing numbers and symbols. Dramatic film noir lighting with deep shadows and venetian blind stripes cutting across the wall. Color palette of deep teals, burnt oranges, and cream whites typical of vintage poster art. The lurking figure wears a fedora hat casting shadow over their eyes. Subtle visual elements of shipping boxes and postal imagery scattered in the background corners, rendered in that classic retro advertising illustration style with visible brush strokes and slightly grainy texture.
